Title: Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 Teaser Trailer
Comment: My quick review: This is nowhere near as good a movie as Guard of Galaxy 1. Some of the visuals are even better than part 1. The first half of the movie dragged on. The main problem was the dialogue was a lot of bathroom humor and goofy bad jokes (and I know this franchise is supposed to have some goofy humor, but it was wayyy overdone) Some of the jokes, and I could care less about censorship or adult humor, were downright disgusting, as in gross. The second half had some excellent action scenes but the action scenes in part 1 seemed better choreographed or something. I would rate it a C+ or B- and part 1 I would give an A. Plot and characters were all over the place. Even for a purposefully light funny and goofy action movie, the jokes mostly fell flat. Worth seeing but nowhere near as cohesive as part 1. Dialogue in action sci fi and comic book movies seems to be getting more and more off-the-wall and silly every year. Every scene does not have to be a snappy dumb one-liner. What happened to serious dialogue?

Title: Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 Teaser Trailer
Comment:
Spoilers ahead. If you haven't watched it you need to. 








So I liked the movie a lot! To be honest movies haven't really been my top priority in the last few years. Unless it has a fantastic story line, good mix of action, adventure, silly humor and depth. I'm all in. Lately movies like that are rare to come by. In this movie it hit everything I had ever wanted! Except for Star Lords father... Which was just a slight let down to me. The more I think about why I didn't like that story line very much is because I didn't feel the chemistry between Ego and Peter, the actors playing them. I'm probably going to get a lot of hate for saying this but I don't think I liked Kurt Russel as Ego... For me, he didn't organically fit in with the rest of the cast. I know whoever is reading this might say, "that may have been the point. He was meant to be like that, he's a temporary character." But as I'm watching the movie I loved golden colony of people and the gang members. as well. Even though they were all against the guardians. Everyone fit their characters but the actor that played Ego did not. In my opinion. I'm actually glad that he didn't survive more so because of that. I'm really sad that Yondu was killed of. He was probably my favorite character in the movie. His growth throughout was so on point. All in all I really did like the movie. I think everything else out weighed my feelings towards Ego. It had a lot of heart and I laughed a lot. If a movie can make me laugh so much like this one did. Its a keeper. Out of all the Marvel movies out there, this series is my favorite!

Title: Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 Teaser Trailer
Comment: Say what you will, but I enjoyed this movie from start to finish. In the first film, we were introduced to the Guardians of the Galaxy with these bright and colorful characters, worlds beyond imagination, and a story that sets as an introduction so memorable. With the second film, we got a story that furthers the adventures of our favorite characters. We got some more funny moments, plus character development from certain characters if you've seen the film. Plus, I found the villain a lot interesting as Marvel Villains go. The story gets even darker, but at the same time, it keeps you enlightened. Our fav characters are still here we love it. Plus, BABY GROOT EVERYBODY!!!!!!! Personally speaking, I loved this film as it is.

Title: Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 Teaser Trailer
Comment: I can't wait until the movie where all of the heroes in the movies will come together.  Since all of these movies are leading up to the Infinity Wars, you know it will happen.  It has to since the Infinity Stones we know of all scattered and being contained in different places with the Power Stone being held by Nova Corps, Asgard having the Space Stone, Vision getting his power from the Mind Stone, Doctor Strange having access to the Time Stone and the Collector holding the Reality Stone (we don't know where the Soul Stone is at, but I have a feeling The Vulture will have it in Spider-Man: Homecoming since one of The Vulture's abilities was to drain people's lifeforce, which is something the Soul Stone would obviously be able to do).  And in the end, Thanos will have to begin an invasion to obtain each one, and as we saw in Avengers: Age of Ultron, he's pretty much on the prowl.  So in the end, all of the heroes in these will obviously have to come together.  It wouldn't be a connected universe if it didn't happen (then again, there's no chance of seeing the Netflix heroes or Ghost Rider from Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. coming in, so that does kind of suck).
